27: The countries in South America that are not considered part of Latin America are Guyana, Suriname, and French Guiana. 41: The short-tailed chinchilla is native to the Andes mountains in South America, specifically found in countries such as Chile, Argentina, Bolivia, and Peru. Today, their wild populations are primarily limited to certain regions within these countries, especially in rocky, arid, and mountainous areas at elevations between 3000 and 5000 meters. Due to habitat loss and hunting, wild populations have significantly declined, and they are now mostly found in captivity or protected reserves.
